like operator use 
select * from employees where name like "____";
like here 4 underscore are taken so that it only take names with starting of their 4 characters


use of limit
tells us the number of rows that we have to return

select * from employees limit 3,3;

first 3 tells us the row to skips and then the next number tells us the number of rows that we have to print 

// extract the departments that how many department are present like returing the count of the departments

select count(distinct dept) from employees;

use of group by and aggregate fnc 
example we need the count of the employees in a particular department 

select dept,COUNT(fname) from employees group by dept










